<sec>
<st>
Isotopes</st>

<p>

<indent level="1">

<it>Main article: <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../225/2527225.xml">
Isotopes of nobelium</link></it>
</indent>

Seventeen <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../245/37245.xml">
radioisotope</link>s of nobelium have been characterized, with the most stable being 259No with a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../606/13606.xml">
half-life</link> of 58 minutes. Longer <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../606/13606.xml">
half-lives</link> are expected for the as-yet-unknown 261No and 263No. An isomeric level has been found in 253No and K-isomers have been found in 250No, 252No and 254No to date. </p>

